\begin{equation}\label{v3sube4}x=4-2y-2z.\end{equation}
Substituting $\eqref{v3sube4}$ into $\eqref{v3sube2}$, we obtain
\[(4-2y-2z)+3y+3z=5\]
i.e.,
\begin{equation}
\label{v3sube5}y+z=1.
\end{equation}

